'''Rayan Vitor Simplício Rocha''' (born 3 August 2006), known simply as '''Rayan''' ({{IPA|pt-BR|ʁaˈjɐ̃}}), is a Brazilian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right winger]] or [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{English football updater|AFCBourn}} club [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] and the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]].

==Club career==
=== Vasco da Gama ===
Born in [[Rio de Janeiro]], Rayan joined [[CR Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]] at the age of six.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dabase.com.br/rayan-atacante-do-sub-11-do-vasco-chama-atencao-no-sao-januario/|title=Rayan, atacante do Sub-11 do Vasco, chama atenção no São Januário|trans-title=Rayan, Vasco Under-11 striker, draws attention at São Januário|date=18 April 2017|accessdate=16 December 2022|website=dabase.com.br|language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref name=globo>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/vasco/noticia/2022/11/14/prestes-a-assinar-primeiro-contrato-com-o-vasco-rayan-foi-o-destaque-da-base-em-2022.ghtml|title=Prestes a assinar primeiro contrato com o Vasco, Rayan foi o destaque da base em 2022|trans-title=About to sign his first contract with Vasco, Rayan was the highlight of the base in 2022|first=Emanuelle|last=Ribeiro|date=14 November 2022|accessdate=16 December 2022|website=ge.globo.com|language=Portuguese}}</ref> He established a name for himself as a prolific goal-scorer, scoring 280 goals by the age of eleven.<ref name=valkmar>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/vasco/noticia/filho-de-valkmar-coleciona-gols-no-vasco-e-e-promessa-de-artilheiro.ghtml|title=Filho de Valkmar coleciona gols no Vasco e é promessa de artilheiro|trans-title=Son of Valkmar collects goals at Vasco and is a promise of top scorer|first1=Felipe|last1=Schmidt|first2=Leonardo|last2=Magliano|date=29 September 2017|accessdate=16 December 2022|website=ge.globo.com|language=Portuguese}}</ref> He continued this form into Vasco's under-17 team, scoring 29 goals in 34 games in 2022, catching the eye of Spanish side [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://esporte.ig.com.br/futebol/2022-11-11/vasco-adota-cautela-com-utilizacao-de-fenomeno-da-base.html?Foto1|title=Rayan impressiona, mas Vasco adota cautela com utilização da promessa|trans-title=Rayan impresses, but Vasco is cautious with using the promise|first=Felipe|last=Silva|date=11 November 2022|accessdate=16 December 2022|website=esport.ig.com.br|language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/rayan-apuesta-deco-cantera-barca-13676518|title=Rayan, la apuesta de Deco para la cantera del Barça|trans-title=Rayan, Deco's bet for the Barça youth system|first=Joaquim|last=Piera|date=19 May 2022|accessdate=16 December 2022|website=sport.es|language=Spanish}},</ref>

In [[2023 CR Vasco da Gama season|2023]], Rayan made his professional debut at age 16, becoming the youngest player to play for Vasco da Gama's professional team in the 21st century.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-19 |title=Rayan se torna o mais novo a atuar pelo Vasco no século 21 |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/vasco/noticia/2023/01/19/rayan-se-torna-o-mais-novo-a-atuar-pelo-vasco-no-seculo-21.ghtml |access-date=2026-02-19 |website=ge |language=pt-BR}}</ref> He came on as a substitute in the second half of the 1–1 draw against [[Audax Rio de Janeiro Esporte Clube|Audax]] in the [[2023 Campeonato Carioca|Campeonato Carioca]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-20 |title=Vasco termina empate contra o Audax com 19,8 anos de média de idade em campo |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/vasco/noticia/2023/01/20/vasco-termina-empate-contra-o-audax-com-media-20-anos-de-idade-em-campo.ghtml |access-date=2026-02-19 |website=ge |language=pt-BR}}</ref> In the [[2023 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]], he scored his first goal for the professional team in a 2–1 defeat against [[SC Internacional|Internacional]] at [[Estádio Beira-Rio]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Internacional 2 x 1 Vasco {{!}} Campeonato Brasileiro: melhores momentos |url=https://ge.globo.com/rs/futebol/brasileirao-serie-a/jogo/11-06-2023/internacional-vasco.ghtml |access-date=2026-02-19 |website=ge |language=pt-br}}</ref> In [[2025 CR Vasco da Gama season|2025]], Rayan gained more playing time in the starting lineup with the arrival of coach [[Fernando Diniz]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |title=Rayan vive reviravolta no Vasco com Fernando Diniz |url=https://www.terra.com.br/esportes/vasco/rayan-vive-reviravolta-no-vasco-com-fernando-diniz,d7734953548de7f996d82887cb61a7eakkblkspd.html |access-date=2026-02-19 |website=Terra |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Marques |first=Rafael |date=2025-08-13 |title=Da aproximação do Palmeiras à exigência do Vasco: como futuro de Rayan agita bastidores |url=https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/mercado-da-bola/artigo/_/id/15540748/aproximacao-palmeiras-exigencia-vasco-como-futuro-rayan-agita-bastidores |access-date=2026-02-19 |website=ESPN.com |language=pt}}</ref> He helped Vasco reach the [[2025 Copa do Brasil finals|final]] of the [[2025 Copa do Brasil|Copa do Brasil]], scoring one goal and initiating the play that led to the other goal in the semi-finals against rivals [[Fluminense FC|Fluminense]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Vasco vence Fluminense de virada pela Copa do Brasil - Confederação Brasileira de Futebol |url=https://www.cbf.com.br/futebol-brasileiro/noticias/copa-brasil/a/vasco-vence-fluminense-de-virada-pela-copa-do-brasil#:~:text=Num%2520jogo%2520cheio%2520de%2520emo%C3%A7%C3%A3o,14)%252C%2520no%2520mesmo%2520est%C3%A1dio. |access-date=2026-02-19 |website=www.cbf.com.br |language=pt-br}}</ref> Rayan finished the season receiving the [[Prêmio Craque do Brasileirão#Best Newcomer|Best Newcomer Award]] for the [[2025 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-12-08 |title=Rayan, do Vasco, é eleito a revelação do Brasileirão 2025 |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/vasco/noticia/2025/12/08/rayan-do-vasco-e-eleito-a-revelacao-do-brasileirao-2025.ghtml |access-date=2026-02-19 |website=ge |language=pt-BR}}</ref> and was named to the Team of the Year in the 2025 Copa do Brasil.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2025-12-23 |title=CBF define seleção da Copa do Brasil com oito do Corinthians e dois do Vasco; veja os nomes |url=https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/copa-do-brasil/artigo/_/id/16113818/cbf-define-selecao-copa-do-brasil-oito-corinthians-dois-vasco |access-date=2026-02-19 |website=ESPN.com |language=pt}}</ref>

On 12 December 2025, Rayan signed a new contract with Vasco da Gama until December 2028.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 December 2025 |title=Vasco acerta a extensão de contrato do atacante Rayan até dezembro de 2028 |trans-title=Vasco completes contract extension of forward Rayan until December 2028 |url=https://vasco.com.br/vasco/vasco-acerta-a-extensao-de-contrato-do-atacante-rayan-ate-dezembro-de-2028/ |access-date=15 December 2025 |publisher=[[CR Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]] |language=pt}}</ref>

=== Bournemouth ===
[[File:Rayan 09052026 (1).jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|Rayan with [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] in 2026]]
On 27 January 2026, Rayan signed for [[Premier League]] club [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] until June 2031.<ref>{{Cite web |last=AFCB |date=27 January 2026 |title=Exciting Brazilian prospect Rayan signs for the Cherries |url=https://www.afcb.co.uk/news/2026/january/27/exciting-brazilian-prospect-rayan-signs-for-the-cherries-/ |url-status=live |access-date=27 January 2026 |website=AFC Bournemouth club website.}}</ref> The transfer was reported to be worth £24.7 million, including £5.6 million in potential add-ons.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cvgpzeyq1pno|title=Bournemouth sign Brazilian teenager Rayan for £24.7m
|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=27 January 2026|access-date=27 January 2026}}</ref> He made his debut as a substitute in an 2–0 away win at [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] on 31 January, assisting [[Alex Scott (footballer, born 2003)|Alex Scott]] for Bournemouth's second goal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4572659/debutant-rayan-helps-bournemouth-complete-back-to-back-victories |title=Debutant Rayan helps Bournemouth complete back-to-back victories |publisher=Premier League |date=31 January 2026 }}</ref> He made his first start for the club the following week on 7 February, where he scored the equalising goal against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] in a 1–1 home draw.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4576492/afc-bournemouth-1-aston-villa-1-match-report-7-february-2026 |title=Rayan scores on home debut as Bournemouth dent Villa's title hopes |publisher=Premier League |date=7 February 2026 }}</ref> His second goal came in the next match on 10 February, scoring a headed goal to help secure a 2–1 away win against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/bournemouth-come-from-behind-to-beat-everton-42390121 |title=Bournemouth come from behind to beat Everton |publisher=OneFootball |date=10 February 2026 }}</ref> Hence, he became the third teenager in Premier League history to register a goal or assist in each of his first three appearances, following [[Robbie Keane]] in 1999 and [[Anthony Martial]] in 2015.<ref>{{cite web |last=Brotherton |first=Alex |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cd9e14g43zet |title=Everton 1–2 AFC Bournemouth |publisher=BBC Sport |date=10 February 2026 }}</ref>

With goals against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]], [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] and [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] on 22 April, 3 May and 9 May 2026 respectively, Rayan became the sixteenth teenager in Premier League history to score in three consecutive matches, and, with teammate [[Eli Junior Kroupi]] achieving the same feat earlier in the season, the duo made Bournemouth the first club in Premier League history to have two teenagers score in three consecutive matches in a single season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-09 |title=Fulham 0-1 Bournemouth: What Andoni Iraola said |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c1m2ed58pego |access-date=2026-05-11 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==International career==
Rayan was called up to the [[Brazil national under-17 football team|Brazil under-17]] squad for friendlies against [[Chile national under-17 football team|Chile]] and [[Paraguay national under-17 football team|Paraguay]] in 2022; he scored twice in four games.<ref name=globo/>

On 16 March 2026, Rayan earned his first call-up to the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]] for friendlies against [[France national football team|France]] and [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], debuting against the latter.<ref>{{cite web |date=16 March 2026 |title=Brazil: Brentford's Igor Thiago and Bournemouth's Rayan receive first call-ups |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c8eg0y22w2ro |access-date=17 March 2026 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref name="NFT">{{NFT player|104095|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

On 18 May 2026, Rayan was selected as part of [[Carlo Ancelotti]]'s 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |date =18 May 2026 |title=Rayan included in Brazil squad for World Cup. |url= https://www.afcb.co.uk/news/2026/may/18/rayan-included-in-brazil-squad-for-world-cup/ |publisher =AFC Bournemouth |access-date=18 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Rayan's father, [[Valkmar]], also played for Vasco da Gama, representing the club as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] between 1995 and 2001.<ref name=valkmar/>

